answers.body_markdown:
You can make use of [**the `!?` operator** (`Ord k =&gt; Map k a -&gt; k -&gt; Maybe a`)](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/containers-0.6.2.1/docs/Data-Map-Internal.html#v:-33--63-) here. This will return a `Nothing` in case the key does not exist, and `Just v` with `v` the value in case that exists, as specified by the documentation:

&gt; *O(log n)*. Find the value at a key. **Returns `Nothing` when the element can not be found**.

Then we still need to convert that to an empty list. We can use [**`fromMaybe :: a -&gt; Maybe a -&gt; a`**](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/Data-Maybe.html#v:fromMaybe) for that, here we first give a &quot;default&quot; value to use in case of a `Nothing`, and then we pass it a `Maybe a`. In case it is a `Nothing`, we use the default, in case it is a `Just v`, it will return `v`:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;import Data.Map (Map,empty,member,insert,keys,&lt;b&gt;(!?)&lt;/b&gt;)
import Data.Maybe(&lt;b&gt;fromMaybe&lt;/b&gt;)

successors :: Ord v =&amp;gt; v -&amp;gt; Graph v -&amp;gt; [v]
successors v (Graph arcs _ _) = fromMaybe [] (arcs &lt;b&gt;!?&lt;/b&gt; v)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

or as [@Bergi says](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58252298/how-to-catch-and-ignore-an-error-call-in-haskell/58252328?noredirect=1#comment102874804_58252328), we can use [**`findWithDefault :: Ord k =&gt; a -&gt; k -&gt; Map k a -&gt; a `**](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/containers-0.6.2.1/docs/Data-Map-Internal.html#v:findWithDefault):

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;import Data.Map (Map,empty,member,insert,keys,&lt;b&gt;findWithDefault&lt;/b&gt;)
import Data.Maybe(fromMaybe)

successors :: Ord v =&amp;gt; v -&amp;gt; Graph v -&amp;gt; [v]
successors v (Graph arcs _ _) = &lt;b&gt;findWithDefault&lt;/b&gt; [] v arcs&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

